sentences: He also wrote the regional hit "God Only Knows" for The Capris in 1954.
In June 1954, the group was signed to Gotham Records, and recorded the Wright-penned "God Only Knows", featuring female singer Renee Hinton on lead.
The Capris broke up after their final single in 1958, and Wright began his solo career.
The single "Girls Make Me Nervous" bw "Love Is Gone" was released on the Wynne label in 1958.
Wright recorded 5 singles for the Capitol label, beginning with "Where Was I" bw "Bye Bye" in 1964.
In 1966, "I'm Walking Out On You" was released bw "Hey Girl".
In February 1967, Billboard reported that his Capitol single "I'll Be There" was predicted to reach the R&B Singles Chart.
Wright was a member of an early 1950s group called The Uniques, in which he played piano.
In the early 1960s, he was a member of a backing group called The Manhattans.
By May the 7th that year, "I'm Walking Out On You" was holding its second week in the Baltimore Top 40.
By May 14, it had made the National R&B Top 40, and was at no 37.
The June 18 edition of Billboard reported his single as a Regional Breakout in New York.
However, its progress in the R&B Charts was doing well with the single, spending 6 weeks there, having made it to no 29 the previous week.
He composed "That's All That Counts" for The Four Larks which was released on the Uptown label that year.
His last single released was "I'm Gonna Have My Day" bw "La La La" on the Virtue label.
